cs.RO, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.PL 

This paper is primarily focused on the problem of integrated task and motion planning for mobile robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also uses formal methods such as Differential Dynamic Logic (dL) and Satisfiability Modulo Theories (SMT), which are commonly used in the sub-fields of logic (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the issue of safety in a dynamic environment, which is relevant to the sub-field of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a compositional design approach, which is related to the sub-field of programming languages (cs.PL).
